{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #865: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. There exists a constant $C>0$ such that, for all large $N$, if $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ has size at least $\\frac{5}{8}N+C$ then there are distinct $a,b,c\\in A$ such that $a+b,a+c,b+c\\in A$. Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{o}s conjectured that\\[f_k(N)\\sim \\frac{1}{2}\\left(1+\\sum_{1\\leq r\\leq k-2}\\frac{1}{4^r}\\right) N,\\]and a similar example shows that this would be best possible. Choi, Erd\\H{o}s, and Szemer\\'{e}di \\cite{CES75} have proved that, for all $k\\geq 3$, there exists $\\epsilon_k>0$ such that (for large enough $N$)\\[f_k(N)\\leq \\left(\\frac{2}{3}-\\epsilon_k\\right)N.\\]  References  [CES75] Choi, S. Prize: no. Tags: additive combinatorics, number theory.","id":"vf_09d11bf5df816cd7","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: jayyhk proof of 865 (state axiomatic) https://github.com/Jayyhk/erdos-lean/blob/main/problems/865/Erdos865.lean.","id":"vf_628011e4bec14e4d","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos865.erdos_865 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos865.erdos_865.","id":"vf_a855027823f6c0e1","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_acef7eadcbcd58cc","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/865.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_09d11bf5df816cd7","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:865","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.",